7. Proxy Construction Framework
The model should not rely on only one spread proxy. It should use a hierarchy of credit proxies.
7.1 Primary regime proxies
These should drive the core model:
•	HYG / IEF
•	LQD / IEF
•	HYG / LQD
•	HYG / SHY
•	LQD / SHY
Reasoning
•	IEF provides a cleaner duration-moderate Treasury anchor than TLT
•	SHY provides a short-duration safety anchor with far less long-rate distortion
•	HYG / LQD captures lower-quality versus higher-quality credit appetite directly
7.2 Secondary diagnostic proxies
These should provide confirmation, not dominate the model:
•	HYG / TLT
•	LQD / TLT
•	JNK / IEF
•	JNK / SHY
Reasoning
•	TLT is useful during major flight-to-safety episodes
•	JNK helps validate whether the HY signal is ETF-specific or broader
7.3 Cross-asset diagnostic proxies
These are not direct credit spread measures but provide context:
•	SPY trend and returns
•	VIX level and trend
•	credit proxy return minus SPY return
•	credit proxy deterioration plus VIX rise
