20. Explanation Layer Requirements
The model must explain why the regime was assigned.
The explanation layer should answer:
•	Why was the current regime assigned?
•	Are HY and IG confirming each other?
•	Is JNK confirming HYG?
•	Is credit diverging from equities?
•	Is volatility confirming stress?
•	Is stress rising, stabilizing, or easing?
Example output text
“Current regime is Risk-Off because primary credit proxies remain below medium-term trend, drawdowns are elevated, and both HY and IG are deteriorating. Credit is weaker than equities, and VIX is rising, which strengthens the defensive interpretation.”
