27. Strengths of This Blueprint
This blueprint is strong because it:
•	uses multiple credit proxies instead of one
•	includes both SHY and IEF anchors
•	keeps TLT as a useful but secondary stress diagnostic
•	includes VIX without allowing it to dominate
•	separates trend from stress
•	requires confirmation
•	checks divergence
•	includes persistence
•	supports interpretable outputs
________________________________________
28. Known Limitations
This v1 blueprint still has limitations:
•	ETF proxies are not pure OAS measures
•	ETF behavior includes duration, carry, and liquidity effects
•	VIX is an equity-volatility measure, not a direct credit measure
•	regime thresholds are fixed, not adaptive
•	no direct recession or default-rate model is included
•	no direct options-adjusted spread series are used in v1
These are acceptable for a production-friendly first version.
