30. Formal Blueprint Summary
Final v1 design
The Credit Spread Regime Model v1 is a deterministic multi-proxy credit regime engine that uses:
•	HYG, JNK, LQD
•	SHY, IEF, TLT
•	SPY
•	VIX
to generate:
•	a continuous credit regime score
•	a discrete regime label
•	transition and warning flags
•	interpretable diagnostics
Core design philosophy
Use:
•	primary credit-vs-safe-asset proxies
•	credit quality preference signals
•	breadth and confirmation
•	equity divergence
•	volatility confirmation
•	persistence
instead of relying on a single spread proxy.
Intended role
The model should function as a robust macro credit regime layer within a broader institutional research stack.
